        <div1 type="body">
            

<p>Natchitoches, June 25, 1827</p>
<p>Col: S. F. Austin,</p>

<p>Dr. Sir, Your favour by <persName>Gen. Fullerton</persName> with some <persName>Mexican</persName>
papers and the account of the celebration of the adoption of the
State Constitution have been duly recd for which you will please
accept my thanks&#8212;The Celebration I will publish <date when="1827-07-01">next week</date>&#8212;The
Constitution I had previously recd of <persName>Mr. J Durst</persName> who is having it
published in a <placeName>pamphlet form</placeName>&#8212;I have given <persName>Mr. Cable</persName> several
<placeName>papers </placeName>to forward you by<persName> Mr. Callaghan</persName> If at any time you should
see fit to forward any news of your <placeName>country </placeName>it will be recd and 
published with pleasure</p>

<p><persName>M Slocum</persName></p>


        </div1>
